    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on several favorable matchups today, with **Luis Robert Jr.** (76.49) and **Kyle Tucker** (74.75) anchoring the offense as our highest-rated starters. **Luis Robert Jr.** benefits from a lucrative matchup against Quintana, where his dynamic platoon advantage (+14%) easily outweighs the minor negative wind impact. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** remains a plug-and-play elite option; despite facing a challenging arm in Imanaga, his strong xwOBA profile and the stadium's wind patterns elevate his performance floor significantly. **Jackson Merrill** (68.06) and **Josh Lowe** (66.42) also present strong plays, providing necessary stability as we leverage their favorable platoon splits to chase production in the middle of our lineup.\n\nThe decision to bench **Gunnar Henderson** (52.11) was the most difficult call of the day, as he narrowly missed the starting cut. While his underlying talent is immense, the optimizer flagged a steep penalty for facing a tough lefty in Early and the resulting efficiency drop-off compared to our active starters, who are better positioned to capitalize on their respective right-handed matchups. Elsewhere, we are monitoring the 45% rain risk for **Josh Lowe** and **Nolan Schanuel**\u2014a situational flag that could force mid-game adjustments if the contest is delayed. Despite the high scoring potential of **Andy Pages** (59.95) and **Nasim Nunez** (58.27), we remain cautious of the volatility inherent in lower-order hitters, even when metrics like wind and SP skill lean in our favor. We will keep a close eye on the final lineup cards to ensure our assumed slots for **Liam Hicks**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Josh Lowe**, **Andy Pages**, and **Nolan Schanuel** remain accurate.",
